quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  13,35,The description of the Paradise promised to the righteous is that under it rivers flow; eternal is its fruit as well as its shade. That is the ňĻultimateňļ outcome for the righteous. But the outcome for the disbelievers is the Fire
  13,36,"ňĻThe believers amongňļ those who were given the Scripture rejoice at what has been revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, while some ňĻdisbelievingňļ factions deny a portion of it. Say, ‚ÄúI have only been commanded to worship Allah, associating none with Him ňĻin worshipňļ. To Him I invite ňĻallňļ, and to Him is my return.‚ÄĚ"
  13,37,"And so We have revealed it as an authority in Arabic. And if you were to follow their desires after ňĻallňļ the knowledge that has come to you, there would be none to protect or shield you from Allah"
  13,38,We have certainly sent messengers before you ňĻO Prophetňļ and blessed them with wives and offspring. It was not for any messenger to bring a sign without Allah‚Äôs permission. Every destined matter has a ňĻsetňļ time
  13,39,"Allah eliminates and confirms what He wills, and with Him is the Master Record"
  13,40,"Whether We show you ňĻO Prophetňļ some of what We threaten them with, or cause you to die ňĻbefore thatňļ, your duty is only to deliver ňĻthe messageňļ. Judgment is for Us"
  13,41,Do they not see that We gradually reduce their land from its borders? Allah decides‚ÄĒnone can reverse His decision. And He is swift in reckoning
  13,42,"Those ňĻdisbelieversňļ before them ňĻsecretlyňļ planned, but Allah has the ultimate plan. He knows what every soul commits. And the disbelievers will soon know who will have the ultimate outcome"